TEXTBOX 1: REFLECTION ON PERFORMANCE & OBJECTIVES
(Covers: Performance vs Objectives, CPD Level, Core Values)
================================================================================

PERFORMANCE AGAINST OBJECTIVES:

This quarter I led the BISS Framework Modernisation — refactoring 135+ legacy 
hard-coded test scenarios into a data-driven, self-healing BDD framework. The 
objective was to eliminate manual maintenance (4–6 hrs/sprint) and false-confidence 
placeholder assertions masking real bugs in a government payment-validation process.

I delivered: 90+ copy-pasted login blocks consolidated into one Background; 405 UI 
locators centralised into ObjectRepository; runtime herd resolver (DBRouter) pulling 
live data from BISS_DATA and BISS_INET; 6-layer resilience (smart waits, dropdown 
self-heal, expired-agent recovery, blacklist re-fetch, scenario retry, soft assertions).

Result: Framework live on Jenkins/OpenShift (March 2026), nightly execution active 
22:00 Mon–Fri. Stakeholders receive pass/fail + evidence docs automatically. Flake 
rate dropped 12% → <2%. Time saved: 6–9 hrs/sprint (~300 hrs/year). Throughout, 
Patrick provided crucial guidance on OpenShift integration, Jenkins setup, and 
credential management — ensuring the CI/CD pipeline is production-ready.

